some quick suggestions i have a three month old great pyr pup i live out in the country with a fenced in large yard i am going to a city that's two hours away and going to another city that's one hour away from home to get stuff and go to walmart my puppy loves the crate he was crate trained before we got him and does really good in the crate he'd go in there himself if i was in the room he only barks if he needs to eliminate someone that lives with me is taking me and she said just leave the dog home suggestions we have a pooper scooper and bags and a pickup as long as he is crate trained leave him home let him out for awhile or walk him before you go and he will be fine he will probably be ready for a nap and sleep the whole time you are gone and if he does have an accident well at least he is safe at home question for you if you took him with you what would you do with him while you shopped the car is dangerous to a young puppy not only from the heat but from the damage he could cause to the car and or hurt himself leave him home he will be fine for a few hours Dog training Dog Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Beethoven (film) Skinny Puppy Blood (computer game) Worms weapons and tools Scooby-Doo SpongeBob SquarePants Road traffic accident Golden Retriever Dairy Hobo Baseball Ocean Beach, New York Dean Koontz The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Public transport Firefighter The Inside Guinea pig Toilet humour Manual transmission Lady and the Tramp Nintendogs Eddie Guerrero The Human Stain Fox hunting Ben Johnson (athlete) One Tree Hill (TV series) Fancy rat Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) First aid Wal-Mart Jonathan Archer Gray Wolf Emergency preparedness RuneScape locations New York City Subway Grand Theft Auto: Liberty City Stories 101 Dalmatians: The Series Daylight saving time Euphemism USS Wasp (CV-7) Siesta Johnny 5 Sin City Pickup truck Passenger car Grand Theft Auto (game) Beltway sniper attacks Socialization Sleeping car Parachuting Stroke Truck Donkey Kong's An